body_html: I also got the same problem after installing tf_nightly using "pip install tf_nightly" with administrator privileges on windows 10. There was another related issue that while installing tf_nightly some WIN ERROR 5 was raised for which the problem stated here occured. I got to know that it was because of an active session running tensorflow. I solved it by shutting down any python programs currently running and reinstalling tensorflow and tf_nightly and it worked like a charm. I hope it helps someone with the same issue.
